    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "An interesting thing to note is that this function was necessary when the minter was the owner, because they might have wanted to keep ownership for other things (e.g. pausing), and still give token holders the guarantee that minting was no longer possible. With the new granular permissions, this problem is no longer there. The minters can renounce minting to achieve a similar effect.",
